articles.title: Indiana woman killed after arriving at wrong address to clean, police say - The Washington Post
articles.description: Maria Florinda Ríos Pérez de Velásquez was shot dead on the front porch of a Whitestown house, police said, adding that the gun was fired from inside the home.
articles.content:
A woman was shot dead after she arrived at the wrong address for a cleaning job, police in Whitestown, Indiana, said.
